        extension: "This same latent heat principle explains why sweating is an effective cooling mechanism — evaporation of 1 g of sweat from skin absorbs 2,260 J from the body. The body can dissipate large amounts of metabolic heat through relatively small amounts of sweat evaporation, far more efficiently than simply warming and losing liquid water would achieve."
