                    ruleForK: "Pure solids and pure liquids are omitted from K expressions — their 'concentrations' are constant and incorporated into K",
                    example: "CaCO₃(s) ⇌ CaO(s) + CO₂(g): K_c = [CO₂]",
                    commonError: "Including solid or liquid concentrations in K expression"
