            "The rate constant k depends on temperature and catalyst but not on concentration",
            "Reaction orders (0, 1, 2, or fractional) reflect the mechanism, particularly the rate-determining step",
            "Integrated rate laws allow calculation of concentration at any time and identification of reaction order",
            "The linear graph identifying the order: [A] vs t (zero), ln[A] vs t (first), 1/[A] vs t (second)",
