                scenario: "Predict whether CH₃COO⁻ + HCN ⇌ CH₃COOH + CN⁻ is product-favoured",
                solution: [
                    "Ka(HCN) = 4.9×10⁻¹⁰ (weaker acid); Ka(CH₃COOH) = 1.8×10⁻⁵ (stronger acid)",
                    "Reaction shown: HCN acts as acid, CH₃COO⁻ as base",
                    "K = Ka(HCN)/Ka(CH₃COOH) = 4.9×10⁻¹⁰ / 1.8×10⁻⁵ = 2.7×10⁻⁵ << 1",
                    "K << 1 → reverse reaction favoured; CH₃COOH is stronger acid, so it wins back the proton"
                ]
