                "Forgetting Tollens'/Fehling's only distinguish aldehydes from ketones — not all carbonyl tests",
                "Mixing up E1/E2 with SN1/SN2 — temperature and solvent polarity control the balance",
                "Assuming all N-containing compounds are basic — amides are very weakly basic",
                "Forgetting phenol does not react with NaHCO₃ (unlike carboxylic acids)",
                "Confusing iodoform test: only methyl ketones CH₃CO– and ethanal (and secondary alcohols with CH₃CHOH– group) give positive result"
